<SUMMARY>
This model computes the utility of accepting an offer by adding the monetary value (split_self) to a fairness adjustment determined by the normalized deviation from a fairness reference. The fairness reference is defined as the participant's token share times the combined earnings. The deviation is transformed via an arctan function—scaled by two learnable parameters (lambda_param and tau_param) that respectively modulate the magnitude and sensitivity of the fairness adjustment. This formulation captures saturating sensitivity to fairness deviations in a parsimonious two-parameter framework.
</SUMMARY>
